annotation.TEXT: Me want coin! (In the original Contra, lying down did actually stretch your hitbox horizontally.)
NOOOOO!!! Nuts! Got unlucky there. Well, I'll just quickly run through Bowser during my mercy invincibility.
Ooh, I like those flower graphics.
Oh, well. It's fine. Now, this level marks the first appearances of both Lakitu (Pidgit) and red piranha plants (Cobrats).
Yes, destroy all of the bricks! MWAHAHA!
Huh. This fire bar block is normally one tile higher than this. I would assume its current position is to help the weaker jumpers, except I'm using Mario, who normally wouldn't need such assistance.
Yeah, I'm not gonna try for those three coins. Also, that sole block down there is probably there to help weaker jumpers, as usual.

Note: This laser weapon is made up of four shots in a row. However, if you fire again while any of your previous lasers are on the screen, the old ones disappear instantly, which kind of hinders this weapon...
This pipe is normally one tile taller, but it being shorter now makes sense, so that weaker jumpers like Bill can get past it.
I'm probably not gonna use that cheat while playing normally for the most part, but maybe I'll find a reason/excuse to use it at some point in the future.
Nuts, I hit it late.

However, I did get a vote to use a random skin of the spread gun user in 4-2, so I'll do that, and for the rest of the W4 levels, I'll be completely random! So, who will be my first random pick today?
...Really, game? Okay, it gave me Lance Bean this time. Maybe he'll acquire an "S" in this level.
Nailed it!
Gotcha! Now, there's a hidden 1-up against the right side of this staircase here.

Ah, the "Wall2" upgrade! (Oh, that reminds me. I've still gotta mention the mashed-together text from the description of the "Wall1" upgrade on the Exploding Rabbit forms. I'll do that now, before I forget.)
Okay, can I time this right this time?
I've sometimes gotten unlucky like that there on the All-Stars Lost Levels as well.
...Or we could find out right now!
Okay, so why am I rescuing Phanto?
I got... a sunburned Bill.
It's-a-me, NES SMB2 Mario!
Bowser's fireballs make this part really tricky. I have to look for safe openings and hope that a fireball doesn't appear in the wrong place at the wrong time.
Whoa, I almost slipped there. That would've been silly.
Oh, man. When did I end up in world 8 of SMB3? It's interesting that it picked these graphics and music here.
To be continued... Yo!
There's an extra platform here that I assume is there to help the weaker jumpers. (Also, despite what it looks like, these platforms aren't slippery.)
Demo count: 5
(Of course, losing the AWESOME SPREAD GUN wasn't awesome...)
This pipe leads to an underwater side area. Good thing I'm using Sophia!
I know that there's another side area in this level, and I want to have enough time for it, so I'm not gonna try to get all of the rupees here.
Nuts, an "F". Well, I'll grab it, since I think I remember there being random Bullet Bills in this level.
..."M"? Darn it. I think I'll keep this "L" then.
There's a discrepancy here! This middle ledge should stretch one tile further to the right!
Oh, no! I don't think I can get past that Laser without picking it up! Argh, I should've thought of that before I went crazy with my AWESOME SPREAD GUN there...
Alright, what random duder will I be using in 4-3?
That was a close call. That Porcupo (Spiny) almost landed on me.
Yep, it takes two hits to destroy a Bullet BIll with this gun.
"F" again. Well, I'll certainly grab it, since it works against the Bullet Bills, if I can hit them enough times, that is.
Alright, time for a random spread gun user for 4-2!
It helps if I can move the cursor correctly, but whatever. So, place your votes now! (Just so you know, 5-2 is an underground level.)
Ooh, nice simple graphics. Now, near the beginning of this level is a super-ultra-mega-large fire bar that I've gotta watch out for.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the vote results for this time, and they're mostly random.
Nuts. Hitting a shell like that gets you 8000 points in the original SMB games. Oh, well.
Careful, there's an evil black mushroom here.
Oh, these graphics are Awesome.
Okay, I think I'll have just enough time to show the two hidden blocks along the right side of the ending staircase here.

Wait, I just noticed something... The timer read 111 when the screen transitioned, but it started at 103 here. Was it still counting while it was invisible? That's not right! I should mention that on the ER forums...
Bah, I fumbled that quick attempt at 5000 + 6 fireworks, resulting in me getting 800 + 0 fireworks instead. But, at least I didn't time out!
I got lucky that none of them fired at a bad time for me! Now, let's grab this Star of David here... (Actually, it's a Hiranya, a symbol popularized by a Japanese radio show called "Young Paradise".)
ARGH!!! I was right about the random bullets, but it takes more than one fireball shot to destroy them...
Whoa, hello!
There's a Hammer Bro. over here which I'll burninate immediately.
You can be sure that I'll be mentioning this inaccuracy on the ER forums!
Now. this part can be tricky. I think it's easiest to take the top route.
It's possible to get a 1-up combo here by kicking this red duder's shell, but I doubt that Bill would have the necessary speed to make that work.
Hopefully I'll be able to find another "S" somewhere.
Lance tags out and we go back to Bill. ...Huh? Is it just me, or does that portrait look almost like Guile from Street Fighter II?
Okay, there are some cannons at the start here that worry me...
The first pipe down there leads to a bonus room that I hope will give me an "S".
Should I get those last three coins? Yeah, sure. Why not?
Whoa, hello!

Now, there are hidden blocks here, with a power up in the upper right one, and normally, there wouldn't be a gap that I could jump through to get from the bottom path to the middle path, but as I just mentioned, that middle ledge is one tile too short, leaving that gap.
LOL, blocky Atari-like enemies.
So, which random duder will take on the castle?
Okay, now I can safely reveal it, and then collect some coins over here.
This brick contains a vine leading to the second side area. However, I do know that it sends me to an earlier point in the level, so I'd better not waste too much time...
Man, for a moment there, the bullets just kept spawning up high.
The rightmost ? block there has a poison mushroom, which I'm trying not to reveal yet.
Okay, so world 4 is done! Who should I use for world 5?
That is really cool! I bet I unlocked that by grabbing a certain number of ammo pickups.
Since I have all of Sophia's upgrades, power up blocks will just give me ammo now.
Run! Run! Hurry! Hurry!
I don't know why the video stuttered there. Random PC lag, I guess.
It's Sophia J-7... The exact same one that I used in 3-2 last episode... You guys did see me pick "Random" there, right? And I did hit the random skin button, too.
Find out next time!
This pair of blocks right before the floating pipes is one tile lower than usual, I assume to help weaker jumpers.
Whoops, meant to use a homing missile there.
Man, if I had more time, I'd definitely try for a perfect here, but I've really gotta hurry and get out of here if I don't want to time out!
Also, upon further investigation, this fire bar is rotating the wrong way as well. I think I'll mention this on the ER forums.
If I wasn't low on time, I might've circled around to the left and gotten that flower, but whatever. It's not important, since I'm already fiery.
There's another super-duper-elongated fire bar right here.
